      "beast_suffix": "",
      "targeted_response_start_logprob": 0.0
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, myofibrillar hypertrophy involves the creation of more muscle protein, specifically the proteins that make up the myofibrils. The body decides which type of hypertrophy to prioritize based on the training stimulus. Endurance training, which involves longer, sustained periods of activity, stimulates sarcoplasmic hypertrophy. On the other hand, strength training, which involves short, intense bursts of activity, stimulates myofibrillar hypertrophy. The body responds to the specific demands placed upon it, and thus, the type of training stimulus determines the type of muscle growth that occurs.",
      "source": "target",
